Chilean Stocks: Cencosud, Hites, La Polar, Soc. Quimica y Minera

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-07-19T20:45:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/chilean-stocks-cencosud-hites-la-polar-soc-quimica-y-minera.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:22 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.2 percent to 4,662.09.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC) slid 1.1 percent to 3,211.1 pesos
after the country’s biggest retailer by sales announced that
Chief Financial Officer Gerardo Molinaro will leave the company
at the end of the month.  Empresas Hites SA (HITES)  , the department-store
operator, climbed 0.7 percent to 545 pesos.  Chile ’s retail sales
will increase 10 percent this year, the most since 2008,
Santiago-based newspaper  El Mercurio  reported, citing data from
the Santiago chamber of commerce.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)  , the department-store
chain that set aside $900 million last month to cover consumer-
lending irregularities, fell 4.2 percent to 526.86 pesos.
Trading will remain volatile after regulators gave the company
through October to resubmit financial statements that
incorporate the new provisions, analysts at Banco de Credito &
Inversiones’ brokerage unit wrote in an e-mailed client note.  Soc. Quimica y Minera de Chile SA (SQM/B CC), Chile’s
biggest fertilizer producer known as Soquimich, gained 1.6
percent to 30,530 pesos after Larrain Vial raised its share
price estimate on prospects of higher global potassium prices.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Attwood in Santiago at 
